reviewText: Nothing but All-of-Bests. All the way from Kanya-Kuwari to Kashmir, and from Kuttcha to Assam, Sikkim, Nagaland, and Burma.
do nor waste your time with this movie
could have been made better! too predictable
this was very different than what im used to seeing ajay devgan.i had no idea he was so silly. very funny movie.i would recommend this to any ajay fan

worst movie... height of hopelessness... it's below standard even for a David Dhawan movie.
Total disappointment.
This is a Bollywood remake of Dirty Rotten Scoundrels. This has some funny moments in it and worth watching once.
It's not that great, but still fun to watch if you have nothing to do.
Slap stick comedy. Watch if you have nothing else to do in life.
Stupidly funny. Good if your just up for a laugh.

This was soooo much fun to watch. The saying, "what goes around comes around" is exemplified in within the first couple of frames when the two rascals meet for the first time. Later it is revealed again as the two "Rascals" fight for the love of their lives.

The movie is all about two conmen Sanjay Dutt and Ajay Devgan. It is all about them conning each other and then they fall in love with the same girl, who cons them in return. Its boring, completely sexed up, no intellect. Better not to watch it than ending up with a headache!!.
A good 'No brain' comedy movie. Sometime its feel like torture.
This is the worst movie ever!
I generally never turn off a movie once started but this was beyond STUPID.  I would never recommend this movie.  Complete Garbage.
Horrible to say the least.  Limp storyline & ever limping acting
Below standard jokes for such a high caliber cast
